						<summary>

						<p><hi rend="italic">Stone in S. No. 393.</hi></p>						

						<p>This inscription in characters of about the <hi rend="bold">8th century A.D.,</hi> states that when <hi rend="bold">Śrī-Māra</hi> was governing the <hi rend="italic">nāḍu</hi> a hero named Gōvinda died in a cattle-raid. The woman named <hi rend="bold">Binnapōṭi</hi> erected the memorial stone which was engraved by <hi rend="bold">Guṇaga.</hi></p>						

						</summary>
